<item>
            <title>[FELIX-2030] Webconsole cannot handle relative paths</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2030</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Similar as &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2000&quot; title=&quot;Pathinfo for servlets/filters with relative path not correctly determined &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FELIX-2000&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FELIX-2000&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; when embedding Felix inside a Tomcat WAR which also registers Felix&apos;s HttpProxy on a relative path the webconsole does not work correctly anymore. All (generated) links don&apos;t take the relative path of the servlet into account. For example, when mounting the HttpProxy on /foo (which should cause the systemconsole to be accessed through &quot;/foo/system/console&quot;) the Webconsole creates links like &quot;/system/console/bundles&quot; and such.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Tomcat 5.5 with Apache Felix 2.0.4</environment>
        <key id="12455145">FELIX-2030</key>
            <summary>Webconsole cannot handle relative paths</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
